	   <tr><td colspan=2>With a small popping sound, Culris appeared before the empress in the Tower of Death.  Bowing briefly, and glancing over at the monkish skeletal pet attending Usula, he informed her of the encounter with Pusbag.  He finished his report by saying, “He planss to be here by week end, Empress.  We do not know his mode of travel, for surely he shall not be able to retake Grobb and still make the boat leading to Overthere in time.”<br><br>“In that you are correct, Culris.  Though Grobb displeases us to some measure, it is still quite a defensible place.  Perhaps even We have underestimated the power of this troll.”  Culris trembled in fear.  Never in his long memory had the Empress used to formal plural when they spoke in private.  “Where are the Three now, Culris?”<br><br>Bowing, Culris said, “My mistress, they remain on Antonica, and have been scouting the lands of the Innothule swamp.  I thought it would work to Your advantage that they know the lay of the land, since Your Highness has declared that it shall be the place the royal personage lounges during the summer months.”<br><br>Usula smiled; clearly seen ivory sharp teeth gleaming.  “You have pleased me Culris.  This may yet turn into advantage for our people.  I have sent several other agents to assist Pusbag in the retaking of Grobb.  Return to the Three and make sure that none escape the glorious wrath Pusbag shall reign down on the traitorous frogloks within Grobb.”<br><br>“What of the Icewind, Empress?”<br><br>“Concern yourself not with that, dear Culris… it is well in hand… indeed, very well in hand.”<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane-Infection<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
