<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100922662544339></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100922662544339><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100922662544339>A day of reckoning for the traitors</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100922662544339#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag the Malevolent</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1247 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 24th 3:43 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Pusbag re-examined the document in his massive hands delivered to him by magical means.  The letter reaffirmed a sneaking suspicion he had had since leaving Grobb, a suspicion that demanded his immediate attention.<br><br>The seven traitorous Trolls snored loudly by the campfire while the eighth kept watch in the wee hours of the morning.  Pusbag smiled wickedly to himself.  He would allow them their rest before an accounting of their actions would be required.  After all, what was sport in the disposal of sluggish foes unable to properly defend themselves?  He pulled out his scepter from his Spirit Pouch and began to polish an already gleaming weapon to an even further burnished glow.  The orange embers of the fire gave a flickering aura to the Emperor's savage expression, making him appear as though a cacodemon has possessed his soul; which perhaps come morning might just happen.<br><br>As the dawn began to creep over the horizon the sleeping Trolls began to stir, their insatiable stomachs waking them up.  As their eyes opened they were greeted with the vision of Pusbag fully dressed for combat in his spike-laden totemic helm and mail.  &quot;Wake up, ladies.  It is time to practice our skills!&quot;, he snarled.  The guards quickly gulped down some vittles and donned their armor while lining up in formation.<br><br>Emperor Pusbag strode up and down the line critically examining his troops while casually swinging his enchanted mace.  After a moment he stopped pacing and in a low voice he asked, &quot;What?  Did you not even think I was prepared for the possibility of treachery?  I might have not known the exact moment you would attempt to betray me, but I have sensed that your hearts were not loyal from the time we left Grobb.  Tell me-- what reward were you offered that you thought you might spend in the afterlife?  That, after all, was your fate when you accepted your wage!  <br>So I want an answer.  Who is this who corrupted you from your true Master?&quot;<br><br>The complement of royal guardians looked at each other in fear wondering who among them had slipped and revealed their purpose.  &quot;Answer me!&quot;, roared the enormous Troll leader.  The head of the guard stepped forward and with false bravado said, &quot;Grand Vizier, errr, I mean King Totem is our benefactor!  He has promised us great wealth and power for performing this task for him.&quot;<br><br>Pusbag began to shake with laughter.  &quot;<b>King</b> Totem?!?  Is that what he aspires to?  You sold your soul to a mere king?  You were my trusted palace guard, the protectors of an <b>Empire</b> and you traded down to a pathetic kingdom?  Well, now you shall pay the price of your folly.  Take up your weapons and let's have at it!&quot;<br><br>With those words Pusbag began to sing an incantation with a gravelly voice.  A single yellow strand of magic slipped from his mouth and wrapped itself around his massive form.   The spell &quot;Strength&quot; caused his already muscular form to become misshapen with a chaotic bunching of knotted cords, making his armor bulge alarmingly near the seams.  Immediately he began another series of spells just as the royal guards started to encircle their prey.  A deadly light green spray erupted from Pusbag's fingertips causing the traitors to gasp in fear sucking the virulent magical disease into their lungs.  Wretching and doubled over, they tried to attack the malevolent Troll in their midst, but found in their weakened state they were no match for the nimble High shaman who continued to incant further poisons and diseases upon his victims.<br><br>At last, with a blue flash, Pusbag began to levitate over the fallen guards.  He moved off a ways and with a low keening sound started to call that feared scavenger, the Inthulic Worm, from the ground.  The whining notes emitted from Pusbag's throat were the sounds made by a lucky worm announcing its' discovery of an easy meal.  An entire nest of worms would quickly converge on the site of the find and devour anything edible in the vicinity.  <br><br>The contorted and writhing palacial guard's eyes widened in terror at the sounds made by his Emperor and the repsonding movement in the dirt just below the surface.  The prospect of being eaten alive-- such a reversal of roles since a Troll was normally the creature doing the eating!  The eight Trolls nearly wet themselves in fear since they were unable to stand up, much less defend themselves.<br><br>The ground around the sick Trolls began to boil and move as ten foot worms practically lept from the soil only to dive back in as if it were water.  All at once, one of the Trolls screamed in pain as a large chunk of flesh was ripped from his thigh.  As his green blood soaked into the ground the activity below the surface began to intensify.  Five worms squirmed out, one appearing through the traitorous leader's midsection, its' razor sharp teeth snapping and chewing seeking another piece of meat.  Quickly, the ground was covered with soft, pink, fleshy worms biting and severing flesh from bone.<br><br>Soon, all movement was quenched as the terrible worms finished feeding on the corpses of the slain Trolls.  Pusbag nodded in satisfaction, content in the finality of his judgement.<br><br>As the Inthulic worms slipped back into their dormant sleep below the surface of the earth, three Iksars burst through the bushes.  One, named Culris exclaimed, &quot;Masssster!  We heard the noisssssse and ffffeared the worssssst!  We are glad to ssssssee you are unharmed.  The Empressssss will be mossst pleassssed.&quot;  At the mention of her name all three bowed their scaly heads momentarily in respect.<br><br>&quot;Tell the Empress I will be in Cabilis within the week for our wedding, but first I will deal with the traitor, Totem.  Tell her that this was not unexpected, especially in light of that Vah Shir slipping in and out of my city at will.  I <b>knew</b> that there was someone inside who had provided the means for that Cat to infiltrate my defenses.  We now know just who that somebody is.&quot;, snarled Pusbag.<br><br>The lizards acknowldeged their new orders, bowed low, and left in the direction they came.  Pusbag took a moment to study the wrecked bodies laying before him.  &quot;Hrrrrrrmmmm.  This is just the beginning.  A small warmup before I reestablish my control of Grobb.  Once that small detail is taken care of, I will start on those cursed elves in Kelethin,&quot; he thought to himself.  &quot;Hrrrrr hrrr hrrrrrrr!  This has given me an appetite for more...&quot;<br><br>On that thought he cast &quot;Sickness&quot; on himself to feel the queasy rush of pain, SoWed himself, and began his journey to Grobb.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Dec 24 15:59:36 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
