<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100921604337847></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100921604337847><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100921604337847>In New Sebilis</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100921604337847#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=120456><span id=Guru>QueenUsula</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>69 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 24th 12:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The empress paced around her quarters in West Cabilis muttering to herself.  Her courtiers were outside, in the hall she used to receive the various Iksar guilds and conduct the daily business of running a troubled empire.<br><br>Clutched between her claws was the latest report of softskin excursions into the Lake of Ill Omen.  Though she was secretly pleased that the softskins were doing her and her empire a service by eliminating the goblin and sarnak forces that massed in those areas, she worried that the softskins were becoming too comfortable so close to the gates of her city.  Screeching and shredding the latest report, she sat down on the cold stone and began to focus her mind.  During this process she was transformed into the image of a dark boned skeleton ~ truly a frightening sight.  After what seemed to be hours of such painful contemplation, she stood up calmly, changed her visage once again into the small iksaress with poison green eyes, and entered her reception hall.<br><br>There she met with her war leaders and advisors, who were showing her the latest estimates of the cost in lives and resources the continued support of Pusbag would cost the empire.  Coupled with those reports were the more disturbing ones showing the possible implications if Totem were successful with his rebellion and Pusbag were slain.  Truly, the cost to the Empire would be great if Pusbag failed.  Usula sighed, knowing that if Culris and the Three, as well as those few other servants she allowed to travel beyond Kunark could not save Pusbag, then nothing could.<br><br>Two of the servants approached her bowing deeply.  One of the two, a young necromancer who showed great potential, handed her yet another document, and backed away bowing.<br><br>Glancing down, she saw the mark of the softskin Aaean…<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane-Infection<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
