	   <tr><td colspan=2>The watercraft was small, but swift, as one might expect of an amphibious race.  Reaching the small island off the West Karana coast, it dropped anchor near the clandestine Iksar camp.  Charssk dove into the water and quickly swam to shore.<br><br>Meeting with the Crusader in charge, he gave his report for dispatch to Empress Usula, and was given a note with new orders:  He was to proceed to Grobb with all dispatch, and provide whatever assistance Emperor Pusbag required, then proceed to Cabilis when released by the Emperor.<br><br>Grobb.  He shuddered slightly, at the thought of being surrounded by the odor of so many trolls.  Perhaps, he hoped, the one called Rungupp was one of their worst hygienic offenders.  He could only hope...<br><br>Whatever his thoughts were on the subject, he kept to himself, however.  He should be thankful that the Empress would not get his report until after he had at least a chance to redeem himself.<br><br>Bowing to the Crusader, he departed, and quickly swam out to the boat awaiting him.  As soon as he was aboard, the boat weighed anchor, and set out for Grobb.<br><br>---<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Dec 24 12:18:11 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>21st Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Centurion Politico, 7th Legion</td></tr>
