<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100905434367875></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100905434367875><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100905434367875>Chapter 4,  Unkk</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100905434367875#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag the Malevolent</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1247 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 22nd 3:52 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Growing up in Grobb, while an idylic experience, was not without tragedy and pain.  My best friend, Unkk, had lost his parents in a sad turn of events when he was fifteen seasons.   One evening, after consuming much Jum-jum juice, his folks decided to go splurge on a new set of spells they had dreamed of purchasing for their tiny shaman shop located in the city square.  As they weaved and staggered out to the Hand they realized too late they had made a terrible mistake and gone to the wrong one. <br><br>The next morning a search party found them at the base of the Shadowmen's Hand, eviscerated and deboned, splayed out for all to see in the weak light filtering through the rotting trees.  While retribution was exacted on the wraithlike creatures, no cleric could ever hope to resurrect the eradicated remains of Unkk's parents.<br><br>My family took him in and adopted him as one of our own.  If we were thick as halfling thieves before, we became inseparable after the death of his mother and father.  We did everything together-- hunting, school, pranks --nothing happened without the other being involved.  He was closer to me than even a brother.<br><br>It was my first kill that brought about a change in our relationship.  As I told in a previous chapter, the two of us sought revenge for the bullying of a particularly brutal older Troll.  With his death we were free to assert our leadership over the various gangs of youths in and around the city, setting ourselves up for what would eventually be my kingdom.  However, Unkk deferred to me when it came to instigating trouble and hatching plans, and developed into a sounding board for me to bounce my ideas off of.  He always gave me the truth, pure and unadulterated, free from guile or flattery.  His wisdom was such that eventually the city Elders would secretly seek him out to gleen any advice they might gain from his insight.  He was far too young to hold a position on the Council, but he was consulted all the same by young and old, rich and poor.<br><br>The two of us made a potent combination:  his unerring advice and my animal cunning and merciless violence.  We worked to become the hidden force behind all the city's major policymakers, judges, and bankers.  In time each one in turn came to us and swore an oath of fealty to serve and protect our interests.  <br><br>With the pillars of society utterly in our pocket it was the proper moment for us to grasp the reins of power.  The city of Grobb had been without a king for generations due to a fractured aristocracy, each segment seeking a greater share of control, leaving the Trolls in a weakened state.  The Council of Elders was eventually coalesced from the different noble families to help in the running of the city and to organise resistance against intruders.  No strong leader emerged from this organization for many years, causing Trollen society to accept the council as the defacto form of government.  However, as any Troll knows, we crave strong leadership, and more importantly, a king.  So Unkk and I set out to rectify the situation-- after all, didn't the seers foretell of my kingdom?<br><br>**to be continued**<br><br>--Pusbag Infection <br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
