<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100905010866143></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100905010866143><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100905010866143>Enroute to the Empress...</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100905010866143#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag the Malevolent</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1247 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 22nd 2:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As Pusbag made his way through Innothule Swamp he took the time to notice the finer things in life such as the hanging moss draped over low branches, the deliciously dark and gloomy atmosphere that lingered regardless of the time of day, and wonderful odors that seeped up through the mud smelling of decay and death.  He looked around and saw that there were no Frogloks around to bother him in his repose and decided then and there that while the loss of Lashara and Jaggedoak was a disappointment, there was a silver lining in the massive loss of froggie lives.  Pusbag smiled a huge snaggle toothed grin of joy at the prospect of uniting his kingdom with Usula's to form the Empire which would break the back of Good.  Pusbag's grotesque grimace  caused his royal guard to nervously step back a few feet in alarm, but they soon relaxed when they saw their Emperor wasn't smiling a crocodile's smile, but appeared to be genuinely pleased and happy.<br><br>One of the palacial guard noted the Emperor's mood and thought to himself that it wouldn't last for long once they arrived in Cabilis.  The trap that had been set would spring at the moment that the Troll was least expecting and from a source(s) the King thought secure.  He chuckled to himself counting all the plat he would earn from Totem when he returned for his reward.<br><br>The group continued on their way occasionally stopping to whack some giant water moccasins for a snack, using the huge poisonous fangs to pick the flesh from between their teeth.  The noxious poison made for a delicious aperitif when taken with the snake meat.  Each of them shivered in delight as the deadly elixer slid into their bloodstream.  But as they dined and strolled across the border between Da Swamp and South Ro desert, Pusbag paused to lay out a plan.<br><br>&quot;When we cross into the zone I want to raid the orc camp just on the other side of the ravine.  I will go invisible and move to the interior of the camp.  I will kick the fire so the embers will rise-- that will be your signal to run over the hill so that the orcs can see you coming.  Don't attack, just act as a diversion.   That's when I will crush their skulls in from behind.  Listen to me well!  No one is to fight but me.  <b>I</b> want to be the only one out there killing.  Understand?&quot;  He glared at the squad of soldiers accompanying him.<br><br>The royal guards nodded their heads in unison as Pusbag chanted an ancient spell causing them all to be enveloped in swirling rays of blue mana.  And just like that, Pusbag disappeared and his footsteps receded towards the orc encampment.  After a few minutes of waiting they saw a large plume of sparks from the campfire rising in the waning light of the day and began their run towards the orc lookout atop the hill.  A hoarse orcish shout brought all of the sleepy centurions dozing by the fire awake and to their feet, reaching for nearby weapons.<br><br>All of a sudden the Emperor appeared in their midst with his royal scepter raised high over his head!  The mace began its' downward arc, rushing to end the life of the hapless creature underneath it.  With an explosion of blood, bone, and brains the mace came out the side of the centurion's ruined skull, making a sickening *pop* that could be heard across the desert.  The rest of the orcs turned towards this new and more dangerous threat and shouted a warcry to work up their courage as they rushed the colossal Troll brandishing a gleaming silver scepter dripping with gore.<br><br>Pusbag set himself in a batter's stance as if he were preparing to swat the game winning homerun and swung mightily from his hips as the first orc engaged him in battle.  The overmatched shaman orc was bludgeoned in two, spraying his companions with his precious life's fluids, dappling their armor red in his death.  The enormous Troll waded into the middle of his foes, pirouetted and spun in a strangely delicate but deadly dance.  Pusbag's ballet-like moves were much like the intricate kata performed by skilled monks seen near Freeport.  The royal guard was entranced by this display of combat prowness rarely seen and were reminded why it was their ruler had such a fearsome reputation.  (They were unaware, as most were, that Pusbag has an adopted human sister, named Angiisan, who is the guild leader in West Freeport.)<br><br>When the battle ended with it's inevitable conclusion Pusbag gracefully ran up to his awed guards.  &quot;Well?  Go loot!&quot;, he crowed.  He looked each of his bodyguards in the eye and said, &quot;I am sure that we will have a few more opportunities to practice our fighting skills before we have finished our journey.&quot;<br><br>As they ran off to strip the dead of anything valuable, the royal guard who was in charge of the betrayers shuddered and wondered if this was a veiled threat towards him and his co-conspirators.   He regained his composure and reminded himself of the large monetary reward coming to him for the treachery he was scheduled to commit.  Thinking back to the Emperor's kneeshaking combat performance, he began to believe that perhaps he should have demanded a larger financial stake in the coup...<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Dec 22 16:36:04 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
