	   <tr><td colspan=2>Usula returned from her trip to Grobb as Pusbag departed to hunt down those who would tear up his royal decrees, and began to gather her closest advisors.  She appointed Culris, a fellow necromancer of the Wurmbane brood and part of her own clutch (as well as her first advisor), to research the materials from the Innothule swamp she had gathered.<br><br>She then called upon Hierophant Zand, the court chronicler and Warbaron Eator, demanding that they gather together a full legion of troops (both Shadow Knight and Warrior) for an offensive upon Fironia Vie.  The offensive was to be ready within a week's time.<br><br>Late that evening, she called Culris back into her own quarters.<br>&quot;Culris, one of my brood, I have a particular quest I wish you to go upon.&quot; <i>She never used the royal plural when speaking privately to Culris</i>.<br>&quot;As you command, my mistresss&quot; Culris hissed, his orange eyes practically gleaming with wickedness.<br>&quot;Go, with four of the Nihilists, and hunt down the pest Ironhom Hammerforge.  He plagues the lands near the lake of ill omen.  Do not kill him, but secret him into the city, and bring him to <b>me</b>.  I must have him before the week is out.  Remember, do not kill him, and do not fail.&quot;<br>&quot;I obey in all things, mistresss&quot; Culris hissed as he disappeared into the shadows.<br><br>Usula smiled as she began her meditative trance, which passes for sleep with the Iksar.<br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane-Infection<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
