	   <tr><td colspan=2>Section I:  The hatching<br><br><i>I am he who records the workings of the Iksar.  I am without name, without brood, without guild affiliation.  Know then that I record truth, dispassionate and uncolored. </i><br><br>In the year of the reign of no king or emperor, in the city of New Sebilis.<br><br>The eggs had been separated, as was indicated by the Hierophant Oxyn, for all Iksar are predestined to take a specific position within the guilds of Cabilis.  This brood was unique in that there were two female eggs in the clutch;  the smaller designated for the Brood of Kotiz and the larger designated for the Scaled Mystics.  Upon the hatching of the smaller, Harbinger Glosk was in attendance, as there had not been a female egg designated for the Brood of Kotiz for many years.<br><br>Let it be known that on the day of the hatching, the Harbinger trembled in fear.  The young Iksaress had eyes of green so deep it rivaled the poison of the Drachnid Recluse.  The Iksaress who would be come the first Empress of the Iksar was born, and the powers of Cabilis trembled.  Usula had arrived.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Usula Wurmbane-Infection<br>Iksar Necromancer<br>Empress of Fear</td></tr>
