<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100838765410692></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100838765410692><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100838765410692>Know Thine Enemies...</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100838765410692#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Scholar>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>65 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 14th 10:40 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>/ooc on<br>Usula posted a message intended for Bejaizen in my journal.  This response is also found there, but in interests of keeping related topics together, I copy it here.  Hopefully, Pusbag, you don't mind.  If you do, you have my apologies.<br>   -Bejaizen<br>/ooc off<br><br>Approaching his home in Erudin, Bejaizen was surprised to find smoke coming from the chimney. Knowing his sister was still fighting in the Orc stronghold of Crushbone, it could only mean that his father had returned. <br><br>The door opened of its own accord, as it typically did when Arjaizen was in residence. Bejaizen hung his cloak by the door and entered the great room, where his father sat reading by the fire. Arjaizen looked up from his tome. &quot;Welcome home, son. How was your journey?&quot; <br><br>&quot;Far too long, father,&quot; the young paladin answered, &quot;but thankfully, mostly without event.&quot; <br><br>Arjaizen's head tilted slightly to one side in curiosity, and he asked, &quot;Mostly?&quot; <br><br>&quot;Well, there has been some disturbing news from the elven realms, that some number of Tunare's followers have betrayed her.&quot; Bejaizen's brow furrowed with concern as he continued, &quot;There is talk of an assault of the Plane of Growth. How any mortals could be so mighty as to attempt such as task is beyond me, but that is what I heard. <br><br>&quot;I also heard of a High Elf - a cleric of Tunare, I believe - who has taken up her defense as a task. I have pledged my aid in this endeavor, if my aid can be of use.&quot; <br><br>Arjaizen stood and walked over to a small desk, where lay a folded parchment, sealed with blue wax. The seal was stamped with what appeared to be a shield upon which were a snowflake, a blazing sun, and crossed lightning bolts. It was addressed to &quot;Bejaizen, Clan Izrhume. City of Erudin, Odus.&quot; The wizard handed the parchment to his son, saying, &quot;Perhaps this message is related your pledge. It was delivered only yesterday, by an Antonican Bard. He told me it originated in Faydwer.&quot; <br><br>Breaking the seal, Bejaizen unfolded the letter and began to read. &quot;Yes,&quot; he confirmed, &quot;this is from Icewind Novastorm, the Elf I told you about. He asks only that I keep vigilant, and send him word if I hear or see anything of the betrayers.&quot; He looked up from the paper, clearly irritated. &quot;What am I, a mere spy? Fit only to slink in shadows and speak in whispers?&quot; <br><br>His father sighed softly. The lad's pride would get him in trouble one day, he felt. &quot;No, my son, he means nothing of the sort. You are seeking those who would confront gods in their own realms. Do you think yourself ready for such a fight? This Icewind is being cautious. The first step in a war is seeking knowledge. 'Know thine enemies,' the saying goes, and the Elf understands that well. Don't let your pride get in the way of your wisdom. If you charge headlong into battle without knowing with whom you fight, that is a good way to get your head removed. <br><br>With a resigned snort, Bejaizen nodded. &quot;Yes. Yes, of course. I will remember that.&quot; <br><br>&quot;See that you do. Now, was there anything else of interest on your trip?&quot; <br><br>&quot;Oh, nothing much. Just this.&quot; He pulled a crumpled piece of parchment from his pocket and handed it to his father. &quot;Some deluded troll calling himself the Emperor. Imagine that.&quot; <br><br>Reading the paper, Arjaizen's face grew ashen. He spoke softly to himself, &quot;...King Pusbag and the Iksar queen allied... a marriage of convenience? ...Emperor? This does not bode well.&quot; <br><br>As his father spoke, Bejaizen's smug sneer grew smaller and smaller. &quot;What is it? Who is this troll?&quot; <br><br>With shocked disbelief, his father looked at him. &quot;Did they teach you nothing of the world outside of Odus in your training at the temple? Pusbag is king of the Trolls, and a high priest of Innoruuk! He rules over Grobb and it's surrounding environs with an iron fist. That he might be allied with the Iksar, indeed, ruling over both Grobb and Kunark as Emperor, is not good news at all. <br><br>&quot;Odd though, that Queen Usula would submit to this,&quot; he mused. &quot;Pusbag does not share power, he takes it. If she thinks otherwise, I suspect the new Empress may find herself getting a nasty surprise sooner or later. Either that, or Pusbag will. <br><br>&quot;In any case, have you spoken about this to anyone?&quot; <br><br>&quot;What? No, not really,&quot; Bejaizen replied. &quot;There was some idle conversation in a South Qeynos tavern, nothing more.&quot; <br><br>&quot;Idle conversation,&quot; his father grumbled. &quot;For your sake, I hope none of their spies were in earshot. This is not an enemy you want to make at this point in your life. Your deeds have already attracted local attention. The number of Peacekeepers that can walk the streets of Paineel with impugnity can be counted on the fingers of one hand. If the Troll king's spies see you as a potential future threat, they are unlikely to wait until you reach that potential to deal with you.&quot; <br><br>--- <br><br>The young Iksar entered the dark cave with barely a whisper of sound. His curscale armor, while not offering great protection, was light and silent, and allowed the Swifttail to make full use of his amazing agility and dexterity in avoiding the blows of an enemy. <br><br>Around a bend in the cave tunnel were several candles providing a dim light, which was more than enough for him and the cave's other occupant. That occupant, seeing the Iksar monk enter, stood and greeted him. <br><br>&quot;Greetingsss, Charssk, the powerfully built shadowknight hissed. &quot;What newss?&quot; <br><br>Bowing in deference to the Queen's messenger, Charssk answered, &quot;Crusssader, per your orders, I have followed the elf Icewind. He hasss received word from an ally. A dark sssoft-sskin paladin. I bear copiesss of their messages.&quot; <br><br>The Iksar Crusader took the notes, and read them both. The ugly scrawls of the softskins were hard to decipher, but he had been taught to read several of their languages to one extent or the other. That this note was written in their Common tongue made the task of translation somewhat easier. <br><br>&quot;Ssso, he seeks to aid the Elf? Isss he of any conssequence?&quot; <br><br>The swifttail shook his tail as though unsure, and answered, &quot;Unknown. I had him followed to Qeynosss. He was tearing the noticess of the Emperor off the treess. He boarded the boat to Odusss. I know nothing more.&quot; <br><br>Rocking his head rhythmically side-to-side, the Crusader said, &quot;Very well. Go back about your businesss. If you are to do more to deal with this softsskin, you will be informed.&quot; <br><br>Bowing again, the monk silently slipped from the cave. The Crusader turned the messages over in his hand. That someone allied themselves with the Elf was unimportant by itself. But he was also tearing down the Emperor's proclamations. The Crusader thought little of the Troll king, to be sure, but he was sure that his Queen had plans within plans, and that sooner or later, she would remain as sole ruler of the Iksar Empire, which would extend over all of Norrath. Such was her divine right, and the natural destiny of the Iksar. <br><br>If this paladin was presuming to impede the fulfillment of his Empresses wishes, he would soon learn the folly of his ways. Blowing out the candles, he left the cave, and made his way to the coast. It was time to return home with news for his queen. <br><br>--- <br><br>The knock at the door came in the early afternoon. Bejaizen finished buffing the last smudge off his Midnight Sea Mail tunic and got up, then set it down on the chair in which he had been sitting. It gleamed a deep blue color that he had never seen on any other suit of armor. It, along with the crystallized long sword he had recently purchased, clearly identified him as a paladin even at a distance. It was a badge he wore with pride, and if that pride was a vice, then so be it. <br><br>He opened the door, and saw Ticar Lorestring of the Antonican Bards. Lorestring greeted him, and handed over a letter sealed with a symbol he was unfamiliar with. <br><br>Thanking Ticar, and giving him some coin for his troubles, Bejaizen took the letter and opened it. <br><br>&quot;Greetings Bejaizen Izrhume,&quot; it began. &quot;It seems you have been unwise enough to side with that weak High Elf Icewind Novastorm, and his pathetic plots against the rulership of Pusbag and Ourself. <br><br>&quot;We warn you not to meddle in affairs beyond your scope of comprehension, and demand you withdraw any support you might have offered Our Elven cattle, upon pain of torture. Death is, afterall, a bit dull. (signed) Usula Wurmbane-Infection, Iksar Necromancer, Empress of Fear&quot; <br><br>As he read the closing signature, he felt an involuntary chill, and the hairs on the back of his neck stood on end. How did the Queen of the Iksar know about his pact with Icewind? What plots was she talking about? He had, after all, only offered his assistance in bringing the renegade Elven betrayers of Tunare to justice. <br><br>What had he gotten himself into? <br><br>(more to follow...)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>21st Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Centurion Politico, 7th Legion</td></tr>
