	   <tr><td colspan=2>Icewind quickly scanned the message delivered to him a short while ago regarding the lady Lashara Dyran.  Once again glancing that the instructions sent by Pusbag on how to reattach Lashara's fingers, he chuckled to himself and wondered how Trolls ever managed to survive with such primitive forms of healing.  After packing a few items gathered at the temple in Felwithe, he made is way to Kelethin to pay call upon Lashara.<br><br>After waving off the two guards at her door, he quietly entered her chambers to find her sleeping and slightly fevered.  He woke her with a touch as she deliriously mumbled something about pickling troll.<br><br>Icewind quickly set about and cleaned the gaping wounds, where once fingers had been, and, holding his symbol of Tunare close at hand, began to incant a spell.  Immediately, Lashara began to sweat aloe.  Icewind sat down and fell into a deep meditative trance, while Lashara's fever slowly dissipated.<br><br>A moment, or was it an hour? later, Icewind stood above Lashara and began to beseach the great All Mother Tunare for divine assistance.  Blue strands of magic flowed around Icewind has he continued to chant in the Elder Elvish tongue.  Slowly, the multitude of blue strands of manna swirled around Lashara, who was momentarily blinded by the light of the magic.<br><br>When Icewind looked down, he smiled.  Lashara was resting quitely, with her fingers fully intact, and with the fever broken.<br><br>Sighing, Icewind left the room, and ordered the guards to be doubly vigilant, even going so far as to invoke the will of the All Mother to cover them with the Armor of Faith.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Dec 14 01:31:40 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Icewind Novastorm<br>Koada Dal Cleric of Tunare<br>&lt;&lt;Mith Marr&gt;&gt;</td></tr>
