	   <tr><td colspan=2>/OOC enabled<br><br>Pusbag:<br><br>I am a ranger by day, enchantress by night. Sadly, my magical prowess in the enchanting business extends only to a few newbie male wood elves, a great lot of male half-elves and humans, whom I bear no affectations for, and a particular wood elf Lord. The latter of these is my boone, luckily. Perhaps this clarifies as to my meaning from before. :)<br>As for the removal of my fingers, I am not keen on the concept. While Mugali may revel in sprouting troll fingers, I really am quite squeamish about the whole deal. Perhaps my fingers could somehow remain intact? If not, please find a way to restore them post haste. I really hate the idea.<br>Finally, as to &quot;what the hell we are talking about&quot;, I realized that when you mentioned an upcomming wedding, you were of course referring to yourself and Usula. However my over-amorous conterpart misinterpreted your statement as to the possibility of a marriage between Lashara and Judd. I must admit, that I do not find the idea altogether unpleasent. I do however, find it MOST humorous that Mugali jumped to this conclusion. Is my dear plotting a little suprise for me? <br><br>Mugali:<br><br>What is all the nonsense about my youth? You yourself are of, if I am not mistaken 32 seasons and therefore you cannot exceed me in age by far unless you have, and I stress, the learning capabilities or an ogre. And how does my infancy and your presence at my birth or shortly thereafter affect this plotline and more importantly, WHY????? I feel as though I am lost with respect to the history and background of my own character, which in roleplay, is never a good place to be.<br>Secondly, if my father is so big and important as you claim him to be, please elighten me as to his identity. I had orginally created Lashara to be somewhat of a strong willed, independent, self-made woman. She did not know her parents. If you would like to have some connection to, or make absurd remarks about, my paternity, at least have the decency to explain them to me so that I might respond? Otherwise I become the outsider in a private joke about myself. And furthermore, if by ANY expanse of the imagination you are for one second trying to insinuate that Lashara is Judd's daughter.....I ask you to please reconsider. It would not bode well for future romantic encounters between us, which I believe, is what got this little arpee ball rolling.<br><br>/OOC disabled.<br>&nbsp;<br>Lashara Dyran<br>Keeper of the wolves<br>Hand maiden of Tunare<br>Ranger of the 30th sun<br>Lanys T'Vyl</td></tr>
