<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100868769729182></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100868769729182><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100868769729182>RE: The lost OOC thread</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100868769729182#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85748><span id=Sage>Uniero</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 18th 10:01 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>/ooc on<br>  I really enjoyed reading the thread posted here, it truely does read as a novel.  I am not a writer by trade (was a math major in college lol) and my spelling is terrible (not a problem when writing about Trolls) but I can help flesh out how Judd and Lashara escaped...<br>/ooc off<br>  Uniero wasn't paying attention as he walked through the swamp.  Not a normally a terrible sin, but one that is potentially fatal for a human wandering into the domain of Trolls and not to be expected from a Monk.  He had not been dry for days.  Everything was wet from his robe to his hood.  It was this fact that caused his mind to wander back to another swamp he had recently visited in far off Kunark.  There he had first met the Iskar.  At best he had a an uneasy alliance with the local Iskar clan chief.<br>  &quot;If you kill goblins, we won't kill you was the bottom line&quot; chuckeled Uniero to himself, but the tenious agreement had allowed him to find the wonderous baton in his hands. <br>  &quot;So light and yet so strong...&quot; mumbled Uniero as he ran his hand over the gleaming polished wood.  Suddenly he froze.<br>&quot;Youd hert some'ing over here, Gosmog?  Bah it be nothing&quot;, shouted a large troll. <br>&quot;Shuuda up, you a stoopid one Mos'ike.  I know I hert som'ing&quot;, reponded his partner.<br>&quot;Two trolls&quot; thought Uniero.  One was bad enough, but two...<br>&quot;Both of youse guys be quiet.  What if Lord Pusbag hears youse?  All of us be dead tats what.  Keep looking for dem two elfs.  If Lord Pusbag finds out they are gone....&quot; shuddered a third troll, obviously the groups leader.  <br>&quot;Bah, quit your belly aching Posmic&quot;, yelled Gosmog.  &quot;Lord Pusbag is killing froggies right now, he not know dat dem two have...What's this?...&quot;<br>Uniero had three angry trolls not more than 20 ft away staring right at him.  As one they let out a terrible roar and charged the much smaller monk.  Immeadiately Uniero fell to the ground.<br>&quot;Bah, we scared him to death!&quot; laughed Posmic.  &quot;Gosmog you skin him and catch up to us.  Human's is good eatin&quot;<br>Two of the trolls continued their search for the missing wood elves while Gosmog broke out his skinning knife and prepared to butcher his dinner.<br>Suddenly Uniero jumped up and faster than slow witted troll could belive hit him with a rapid series of blows to the head.  But trolls have tremedously thick skulls and what would of killed a lesser creature simply irritated the large troll.  The temporarily stunned troll simply shook his head, to clear out the ringing in his ears, and stood up.<br>&quot;Bah, you should no trick Gosmog like dat.  Now youse die little man...Huh?&quot;<br>The monk was now standing 15 ft away with his hands at his side.  This infuriated the large troll who let out a roar and charged.  Uniero dropped into a crouch position as the troll approached.  No stranger to fighting smaller creatures Gosmog knew what was coming.  It was a favorite tactic of the dwarfs to run in between a trolls legs, popping out the other side trying to hamstring the larger creature.<br>&quot;Hah&quot; exclaimed the troll as he snapped his knees together to trap the monk, but he caught nothing.  Instead of ducking between the trolls legs the monk leapt high into the air.  It was the trolls misfortune that the act of bringing his knees together caused him to stoop slightly so the flying kick launched by Uniero landed on his jaw with such force as to snap the large creatures neck.  The troll was dead before he hit the ground.<br>Uniero stood looking at his fallen foe.  &quot;I had better find those two elves before his friends do...&quot;<br><br>TO BE CONTINUED<br><br>/ooc on<br>Sorry it went much longer than I had planned.  Will have to update at a later date<br><br>Uniero<br>31 Monk<br>Odin's Ghost<br>7th Hammer<br><br>      <br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
