<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100829186366411></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100829186366411><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100829186366411>Home safe in Kelethin</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=2076&mid=100829186366411#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85616><span id=Guru>Lashara</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>84 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 13th 8:04 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&quot;Welcome back, dear.&quot;<br><br>Lashara smiled at Encina's words. The term of endearment slipped by without a moment's notice. It was a regular thing between the two of them. The two wood elves had been friends for so long, Lashara sometimes wondered if they might as well have been married. Sometimes they certainly acted like it.<br><br>Clad in the spare leathers of her druidess friend, Lashara allowed the more experienced healer to attend to her recently attained wounds. The pretty blonde haired, blue eyed elf before her worked swiftly and with a careful eye. She had already cured the disease her friend has caught from the vile fingernail of The Cuddler, and was now working on sealing out further infection in the leg.<br><br>Encina glanced up slyly, a teasing look upon her face. She did not intend to let the past fortnight's incidents go by unspoken. &quot;You know.....&quot; she began, doing her best to keep a straight face, &quot;The elf who carried your sorry self in here last night was quite a looker. And he seemed to be quite affectionate with you, though that may have stemmed from the fact that you were only wearing a towel while in his arms. Tell me Sister....shall I start learning to bake wedding cakes? I think I should be capable of it within the month if I start practicing now.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Hush you.&quot; The auburn haired one flushed. It had been nice, she would admitted to herself and ONLY to herself, that he had carried her sickened form through those doors the night before as the disease raged inside her. She kept that thought to herself. &quot;You're asking for another melee lesson, on the spot.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Not with my scimitar, you don't!&quot; Encina grinned and rose to her feet. &quot;There. That should patch you up quite nicely, Sister. What an adventure you've had. Battles and romantic interludes with nameless elven men. I am jealous, dear.&quot; And before Lashara could interject that there hadn't been any romantic interludes, her friend continued. &quot;Honestly though, I'm pleased with your work. We're getting the royal treatment here, thanks to you. A twenty-four hour guard outside the door....being put up in the room above my guild, where anyone would be less likely to look for us....it's great fun, really. Just a favor Lash.......next time you see your betrothed....ask him if he has a younger brother I can meet? You're a doll.&quot;<br><br>Lashara sighed. Her friend really was incorrigable.<br>&nbsp;<br>Lashara Dyran<br>Keeper of the wolves<br>Hand maiden of Tunare<br>Ranger of the 30th sun<br>Lanys T'Vyl</td></tr>
